# Next.js App Router Patterns

## File Conventions
- `page.tsx` — route pages (server components by default)
- `layout.tsx` — shared layouts with nested routing
- `loading.tsx` — Suspense loading UI
- `error.tsx` — error boundary (`"use client"`)
- `not-found.tsx` — 404 pages

## Server vs Client
- Default to server components — only add `"use client"` when needed
- Client components needed for: event handlers, hooks, browser APIs
- Keep client components small — push logic to server where possible
- Use `server actions` for form submissions and mutations

## Data Fetching
- Fetch data in server components, pass to client components as props
- Use tRPC for type-safe API calls from client components
- Cache aggressively — use `revalidate` for ISR where applicable
- Never fetch in `useEffect` for initial data — use server components

## Route Groups
```
src/app/
  (auth)/          — login, register, forgot-password
  (dashboard)/     — authenticated app pages
    inventory/
    classifier/
    documents/
    audit/
    settings/
  api/             — API routes (tRPC handler)
```

## Metadata
- Set `metadata` export on every page for SEO
- Use `generateMetadata` for dynamic pages
